# Chiara's World - Cursor AI Configuration

## Project-Specific Guidelines

### Code Style
- Use modern JavaScript/TypeScript (ES6+)
- Prefer async/await over callbacks
- Use const/let, avoid var
- Follow existing code patterns in the project

### File Structure
- Automation scripts in `/automation/`
- Landing page files in `/landing-page/`
- Configuration files at root level

### Code Handling
- Accept code from various sources (Stack Overflow, tutorials, etc.)
- Normalize formatting while preserving functionality
- Add helpful comments for complex logic
- Maintain backward compatibility

### API Integration
- Handle API keys securely (use config.js)
- Include error handling for all API calls
- Use environment variables when possible
- Log errors for debugging

### Automation Scripts
- Include clear console output
- Handle edge cases gracefully
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Support both manual and automated execution

### HTML/CSS
- Use semantic HTML
- Follow Soft Brutalism design principles
- Maintain responsive design
- Optimize for SEO

### Testing Approach
- Test automation scripts before deployment
- Verify API integrations work
- Check error handling paths
- Validate HTML/CSS rendering

